<h1 class="block">FAQ</h1>

<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>How do I find the files I need?</strong>
    <ul>
      In general, you will want to upload 6 files.  They can be obtained by right clicking on the appropriate tab
      in web3 Castle Age and selecting "Save link as..." or "Save Linked File as...", etc.  Assuming you are logged in to
      <span style="color:red">the web3 link</span>, you may right click the link(s) below and save the file on your desktop.
      <span style="color:red">Note that if you are running multiple Facebook accounts, you must log out of the web3 link each time, or you'll end up downloading
      the files from your other accounts instead of the intended one.</span>
      I accept .html, .htm and .php file extensions. The tabs which contain data for uploading are the following:
      <li style="font-size:100%">
        <b>Generals (will not remove generals):</b>
				<%= link_to 'https://web3.castleagegame.com/castle_ws/generals.php',
          'https://web3.castleagegame.com/castle_ws/generals.php' %>
      </li>
      <li style="font-size:100%">
        <b>Soldiers:</b> <%= link_to 'https://web3.castleagegame.com/castle_ws/soldiers.php',
          'https://web3.castleagegame.com/castle_ws/soldiers.php' %>
      </li>
      <li style="font-size:100%">
        <b>Blacksmith:</b> <%= link_to 'https://web3.castleagegame.com/castle_ws/item.php',
          'https://web3.castleagegame.com/castle_ws/item.php' %>
      </li>
      <li style="font-size:100%">
        <b>Magic:</b> <%= link_to 'https://web3.castleagegame.com/castle_ws/magic.php', 'https://web3.castleagegame.com/castle_ws/magic.php' %>
      </li>
      <li style="font-size:100%">
        <b>Lands:</b> <%= link_to 'https://web3.castleagegame.com/castle_ws/land.php', 'https://web3.castleagegame.com/castle_ws/land.php' %>
